Review: The experience here was good. All veg subs (6 inch) are priced at ₹250 irrespective of which one we take. The customer service was friendly and most importantly, place was hygienic. Another thing to be appreciated is that they have separate counters for veg and non-veg which we don't find in many other subway outlets.

Foods are not fresh and it is much upscale as per cost. Variety are sufficient available. Location is prime, exactly at International Airport Bangalore. Outside sitting arrangement ate there and very good ambience. If your flight is delayed or you visited for receiving someone and waiting, it is good place to pass time happily.
Service is quite fast..Take away is available..

Rates are higher. They are charging according to the USA standard. It need to be charged according to Indian standard. Cost of production of raw material is very less even though they are charging higher-ups. Subway cleanelesniss is good and well maintained.

Most of the time I find this as closed or under renovation.
Now probably due to ongoing situation but earlier too.
Or may be my visit n their downtime coincides.

When I’m on early morning flight to Bangalore. This happens to be my first place to eat and relax before staying a day. The Restaurent is very nice & service is very fast. Sometime they don’t have hot beverages. My favorite is chicken salad
Nice eatery in airport.

Very nice spot for subway on your way out of the airport 

Good food quick service too tasty stuff

Very pathetic approach of customer dealing. I have told to be in line and order. I ordered and waited for 10 minutes...They gave my order to someone else.

During late night and early morning flights, I usually chill here before entering the airport. The employees are pretty friendly and quick. You will get your order in your hand in two minutes no matter how crowded the spot is.

Taste was good.  Very convenient to eat while traveling.  Price is exorbitant!!!.

A lot of improvement needed. I bought two foot long sandwiches and asked for them to be toasted. One was toasted too much while the other was cold. The lettuce was dry and old. 
In spite of asking repeatedly not to add some of the ingredients, the person preparing the sandwich for me just turned a deaf ear. This could be due to the fatigue of working long hours because when I got here, it was 2 am. But that should not stop them from serving food at a better quality. The sauce was messy and the packaging was too poor for their standards of customer service.
Traveling from the US, I felt the quality of Subway in India is below par and needs more improvements if they want to stay float in the food industry. I feel it will be better if Subway is inside the Airport and not outside the gates
